Sentencas: Following the previous work on comparing performance of Fickian, Stefan-Maxwell and dusty-gas model for mass transfer in single fuel system, this article is focused on the electrochemistry and transport in the anode of solid oxide fuel cell using H-2-H2O-CO-CO2-N-2 hybrid fuel.
Titulo: Modeling mass transfer in solid oxide fuel cell anode: II. H2/CO co-oxidation and surface diffusion in synthesis-gas operation

Sentencas: Under the standard framework of the dusty-gas model combined with the Butler-Volmer equation, it carries out a macroscopic area specific modeling work.
Titulo: Modeling mass transfer in solid oxide fuel cell anode: II. H2/CO co-oxidation and surface diffusion in synthesis-gas operation

Sentencas: More specifically, two variables of hydrogen current fraction and enhancement factor are well defined and solved for the electrochemical co-oxidation of H-2 and CO, and the diffusion equivalent circuit model is introduced to describe more comprehensively the resistance of mass transfer including molecular/Knudsen diffusion and surface diffusion.
Titulo: Modeling mass transfer in solid oxide fuel cell anode: II. H2/CO co-oxidation and surface diffusion in synthesis-gas operation

Sentencas: The model has been validated well in full region of V-I performance of an experimental anode-supported button cell.
Titulo: Modeling mass transfer in solid oxide fuel cell anode: II. H2/CO co-oxidation and surface diffusion in synthesis-gas operation

Sentencas: An approximate analytical solution of the hydrogen current fraction is also presented for explicit computation.
Titulo: Modeling mass transfer in solid oxide fuel cell anode: II. H2/CO co-oxidation and surface diffusion in synthesis-gas operation

Sentencas: Comparison between the results by different approaches for the effective diffusivity shows the importance of right mass-transfer modeling.
Titulo: Modeling mass transfer in solid oxide fuel cell anode: II. H2/CO co-oxidation and surface diffusion in synthesis-gas operation
